.TH "n_hdlc_tty_read" 9 "n_hdlc_tty_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
n_hdlc_tty_read \- Called to retrieve one frame of data (if available)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" n_hdlc_tty_read
.BI "(struct tty_struct *tty "  ","
.BI "struct file *file "  ","
.BI "__u8 *kbuf "  ","
.BI "size_t nr "  ","
.BI "void **cookie "  ","
.BI "unsigned long offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tty" 12
pointer to tty instance data
.IP "file" 12
pointer to open file object
.IP "kbuf" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "nr" 12
size of returned data buffer
.IP "cookie" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "offset" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the number of bytes returned or error code.
